<br>
AGI is something else I am unsure about. Many claim that it only adds to the total AC number. I am still considering the possibility that it increases damage avoidance, while raw AC from armor increases damage mitigation. Consider (purely hypothetical):<br>
<br>
Increasing AC by 50pts enables you to absorb 20% more damage.<br>
<br>
Increasing AGI by 50pts makes you avoid hits 5% more often.<br>
<br>
The reason that it is seen that pure AC is more important is that raising your AC by 50pts is easier than raising your AGI by 50pts. And since you take less overall damage while increasing your AC by the same amount as AGI, it is viewed that AC is much more important than AGI.<br>
<br>
While I agree that AC is much more important than AGI (tests have shown this), maybe it is not so in all cases. For instance, while fighting a mob with incredible ATK such as Lord Nagafen, I seem to get hit for max damage no matter what my AC is. If I raise my AC by 50 pts, Nagafen is still mashing me like I have no armor on at all. But if I increase my AGI by 50 pts, would I dodge hits better? I would think the answer would be yes.<br>
<br>
I haven't done any parsing, but I am still not convinced that AGI is worthless. In some cases, it may be better to have high AGI rather than high AC. I still concede that in 99% of fights, high AC is better than high AGI.<br>
<br>
Which bracer would be better for overall tanking?<br>
<br>
AC8 AGI+12<br>
AC11<br>
<br>
When equipped, the AC11 bracer gives more total AC. But will you in fact take less damage with the AC8 AGI+12 bracer? If we are comparing a serp bracer vs a silver plated bracer, it would be:<br>
<br>
AC1 AGI+9<br>
AC7<br>
<br>
In this case, I think that the AC7 bracer is far better. We are looking at 6AC vs 9AGI. Whereas, in the previous case we are looking at 3AC vs 12AGI.<br>
<br>
I'm not claiming that AGI has been overlooked. My current equip gives me fairly high AC (920) with fairly low AGI (84), and am pretty happy with it. But I am still considering the true differences between pure AC on items and AGI.<br>
