Here's something for you str geeks to look at. The MN formula :<br>
<br>
Magic Number (MN) = (2 x wpn dmg) + lvl bonus<br>
<br>
This is used for ALL weapons, yada yada. Magic number is basically the number you're going to hit for ALOT of times. This number does NOT change due to str, DOES NOT change. The only things that affect this are level &amp; weapon damage. Not even weapon skill has anything to do with this.<br>
<br>
The level bonus formula for two handers (which has been found to change at 51) is as follows :<br>
<br>
2H level bonus (51+) = (Level -7) / 3<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
That was parsed at level 52 using a 2hb weapon with a 25 dmg rating (Rod Of Lamentation), 128 str, and 205 skill. Those red bars judge how often I hit for a certain number of damage. The more the red the more times I hit for that.<br>
<br>
